pullRequest.body:
As mentioned [on Zulip](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Infrastructure.20for.20tracking.20frequently.20applied.20simp.20theorems/near/475331955):

> `tsub_eq_zero_of_le` got worse in [the unmerged] #17444. It seems that Lean is searching `CanonicallyOrderedAdd` for types that are not ordered at all, then doing some slow unification of instances with metavariables that is impossible to succeed.

---
